                                    embrace continuous learning and collaborate effectively in teams.

                                    underestimation of timelines due to optimistic estimates that fail to account for unforeseen complexities.

                                    8.
                                   Unit Testing focuses on individual components or units of code, such as methods and functions, to ensure they work as expected.

                                    Integration Testing follows unit testing and checks whether different units of code work together properly.

                                   System Testing comes after integration testing and verifies that the entire system meets the functional requirements specified by stakeholders.

                                   Acceptance Testing is the final phase of testing and involves validating the software against the criteria for acceptable behavior as defined by the users or customers.

                                   part 2
                   Prompt engineering is the process of structuring or crafting an instruction in order to produce the best possible output from a generative artificial intelligence (AI) model.


            Write about technology.

            Why the Improved Prompt is More Effective:

    Specificity – Instead of the broad topic "technology," the improved prompt narrows the focus to "artificial intelligence in healthcare."
    Clear Expectations – It specifies the length (500 words) and the aspects to cover (examples, benefits, challenges).
    Conciseness – It eliminates ambiguity, making it easier for the writer to deliver relevant and well-structured content.
